answerText: Kings Canyon National Park[10] Kings Canyon is contiguous to this other national park which contains Moro Rock, Crystal Cave and Crescent Meadow as well as General Sherman, one of its namesake trees.

question: Question: Landmarks of this include Tehipite Valley, Deadman Canyon and Mount Goethe. For ten points each: [10] Name this national park, the headwaters of the San Joaquin River, which contains the General Grant tree.
